@jreback @TomAugspurger 

Installing `moto` from pip seems to work. But `py37_locale` to use indeed Python 3.7 causes some deprecation warnings that I think we should fix:
```
AssertionError: Caused unexpected warning(s): [('DeprecationWarning', DeprecationWarning('time.clock has been deprecated in Python 3.3 and will be removed from Python 3.8: use time.perf_counter or time.process_time instead'), '/home/vsts/miniconda3/envs/pandas/lib/python3.7/site-packages/xlrd/book.py', 74), ('DeprecationWarning', DeprecationWarning('time.clock has been deprecated in Python 3.3 and will be removed from Python 3.8: use time.perf_counter or time.process_time instead'), '/home/vsts/miniconda3/envs/pandas/lib/python3.7/site-packages/xlrd/book.py', 89), ('DeprecationWarning', DeprecationWarning('time.clock has been deprecated in Python 3.3 and will be removed from Python 3.8: use time.perf_counter or time.process_time instead'), '/home/vsts/miniconda3/envs/pandas/lib/python3.7/site-packages/xlrd/book.py', 130)].
```

Can you confirm, and I'll create a separate issue for it?

@TomAugspurger can you check if regardless of the failure because of the warnings, the changes are made are really fixing typos, or if I misunderstood something

>  But py37_locale to use indeed Python 3.7 causes some deprecation warnings that I think we should fix:

I think you can safely add a filter for that specific warning, since it's coming from xlrd and not us. The only reason it's failing our build is because it's bubbling up when we're expecting a different warning.
